if we hadn t found merts on our last day in town we would have eaten here everyday you have to look past the disorganized front desk where one lady was answering togo orders taking names and bussing tables and just enjoy delicious southern soul food they aren t lying when they say soul food everything about the place brought warmth to your soul you can t go wrong with anything you order if you need help deciding the waitstaff was helpful in giving suggestions favorites do not miss merts
